Whenever possible, use structural elements to structure your document. Use built-in headings and lists instead of relying on manual formatting on documents, slides, and tables.
Don’t use color as the only way to communicate information. If you are using colors, make sure to have sufficient contrast.
Put alt text (text descriptions) on images and graphs.
Make sure all videos you are using have accurate captions and a transcript.





